<br>
(credit to Eizabeau for this quote *huggles Eizabeau*)<br>
<br>
I agree entirely. Actually, when I was around last summer and fall, I noticed the same problem actually,, so the problem now doesn't really surprise me. While I appreciate the idea of a guild for raiding, and hunting and such, I came to Firiona Vie, the <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>RP prefered server</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> to see if I could RP. At lower levels, i think it's just as important to start that off right as it is at later levels. Sure the events for such a guild will be of a smaller scale (&quot;Let's raid Befallen!&quot; <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ), and a lot of it would be development and such, but at the same time, I think by the time the teens roll around especially, that people can be tired of trying to associate with other newbies trying to catch up to the vets.<br>
<br>
I understand the problem of re-rollers mind you, and I know that letting in hoardes of 1-5'ers is highly questionable, even to me. But none the less....er, what I'm saying I guess is that I'm interested in forming a new guild, geared towards lower levels right now. It'd have a strong RP element of course (althoguh if I decided to talk about the weather, don't hold it against me). I'm thinking, in D&amp;D terms, the guild would be Chaotic Netral to Chaotic Good. Basically, a bunch of bards, rogues, women, followers of Fizzlethorp and Erolissi in general, Gnomes in party hats, women, ect. Hm, I guess basically the college party of IC guilds or something. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   The only restrictions I can think there would be are stuff like &quot;no preachy Innoruuk people or Mithanial Marr junkies&quot;...but I mean, who else would you turn away from a party after all? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
PLEASE, if anyone is interested, or wants to discuss this idea, POST HERE. I want to brainstorm this, and maybe solve a problem I don't think I'm the only one who sees. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>----------------<br>
