<br>
mmm…..dark elves in leather.  /drool  <br>
<br>
Sadly, I was sidetracked by work and other rl stuff.  I think this would be a great idea, especially if an effort was made to keep bringing in the low levels as the initial membership progressed.  It would also be a nice home for those that do like to try roleplay and have a tendency to reroll fairly often.  (Like, um…me for example *blush*)  <br>
<br>
Actually, I think I’ve finally settled in to a couple of new characters that I’m happy with.  Nathrach is a Barbarian Shaman that is a bit, um….eccentric.    He has conversations with spirits and carries around a pet rock that translates other languages for him.  I found out last night that it is, in fact, physically possible to have your head up your own arse.  Somehow I hit the delete button on the character select screen and killed him.  I have him back now, at level one, and hope to log on tonight and teach his pet rock all the racial languages again.<br>
<br>
Gaillinn is a Human Ranger.  I think he’s about level 7 right now.  Haven’t done much character development with him yet, but I have decided that I enjoy the ranger class and I plan to keep him around for a while.<br>
<br>
I have checked out some of the established roleplay guilds on the FV server, but at the time they had a lack of other low levels to hang out with.  Truth be told, I have also been a bit intimidated.  EQ is my first venture in to any kind of roleplay environment, and the many arguments here on this board about what is and isn’t acceptable roleplay haven’t done much to boost my confidence.  Being worried all the time about slipping OOC and irritating the other folks is a pain too.  I have a feeling there are others out there like myself that would love to give it a try and this would be a perfect opportunity.  I just hope a lot of them read these boards and see this.<br>
<br>
Baby raids in to Befallen and other low level zones sounds like a blast.  I’ve only had two or three pickup groups in all my time here that just wanted to have fun and explore.  Most of them have been all about loot, quick xp, no roleplay, yada yada.  That has driven me to spend most of my time solo and there is much I have yet to experience, even in the low level zones.  I have nothing against the occasional xp grind or loot group, mind you, as long as the having fun part is still the main priority.  And people that whine about the occasional death irritate the hell out of me.  Oh no, I lost xp!  My whole day is ruined!  Uh, hello….you didn’t LOSE anything.  It’s just frigging yellow pixels!!!   (Sorry, /mini rant off)  Corpse runs and rescue parties deep in enemy territory are some of the best times I’ve had in this game.<br>
<br>
I should wrap this up for now, since I’m at work.  I’ll keep an eye out for you in game.<br>
<br>
Oh, one more thing to the community in general.  If you other roleplay guilds have lowbies  sniffin around your doors, but don’t have a place for them right now, maybe you could direct them here.  *hint hint*<br>
<br>
<br>
Nathrach<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=perristhesuave>Perris the Suave</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/20/03 5:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm47.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=500.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://image1ex.villagephotos.com/1877294.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A new train of thought...</span><hr size=1> Well, a few things about what you said, and you touched on some important point about what I was thinking about doing.<br>
<br>
First off, I hope you settle down with a charector soon. I may be somewhat hypocritical saying that (I've had a history of re-rolls for my main on the blue servers), but it's always nice to see someone connect with a charector they creat personally and wish to settle down and develop them more fully. I think, if GoO goes through (and I hope it does), that one of the main things I would try to have it do is support and nurture charector development at that crucial young stage of player charector's lives. Many new players are unsure of what &quot;roleplaying&quot; is exactly. They need to be shown how to be a roleplayer, not what to do and not what to do. Roleplaying isn't about actions, it's about ideas, and GoO would help develop a bundle of stats and patchwork armor into a member of Norrathian society.<br>
<br>
About the baby raids...I think that's also an area I hope to develop. While not totally similar (and in fact, diferent in many important ways), small raids in places like Befallen, Crushbone, Blackburrow, and the Warrens would help prepare lower level charectors for the way larger grouping situations would work (ie, intergroup communication, interclass support, item distributon, ect.). Also, a lot of low level charectors are dumped because the low levels are seen usually as tedious levels of soloing in places where you kep killing bears and snakes and stuff over and over. Baby raids would help low level charectors put a little more fun into that time.<br>
<br>
A few important notes as well. first off, I in part want The GoO to be a &quot;newbie' guild, where (if they want) charectors can leave and join other guilds later on if they wish. This is in part a result of a few reasons.<br>
<br>
1) Coordination - If The GoO is busy trying to orginize a group for raiding Blackburrow, higher level charectors in the guild may feel left out.<br>
<br>
2) The &quot;Feel&quot; of GoO - GoO would be a guild very much oriented towards teaching languages, teaching skills and techniques, helping early RP charector development, ect. Those activities don't lend themselves very well to higher level charectors.<br>
<br>
This isn't to say that i don't think that GoO potentially couldn't <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>have</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> a higher level component. Merely, I mean that I don't want GoO to ever turn into a guild for higher levels. That would defeat the entire purpose of suporting new roleplayers develop. In fact, a part of me hopes that GoO will develop into a cross-level guild, where the veterans help out the newbies for a time, then go on a raid of their own, then go back to helping the newbies again.<br>
<br>
Nath, for contacting me in game, I'm usually on around midnight CST, so that's teh best time to contat me. Don't forget i only speak human for now, so if you have the Barbarian, you'll have to teach his rock thingy quicker. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I'd love to hear from anyone else on ideas, interest in supporting or joining GoO if it gets off the ground, and anything else related to the whole matter. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>----------------<br>
